<a href="#0" id="0">Definition 5</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">The core of a coalitional game Γ is the set of all imputations {a mathematical formula}(p1, … ,pn) that are not blocked by any coalition, so that for any coalition C, we have {a mathematical formula}p(C) ⩾ v Γ (C).</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">Definition 10</a>
<a href="#3" id="3">CSGA CSG is the coalitional game Γ in a coalitional skill domain, where the players are the agents of the coalitional skill domain, and the characteristic function of a coalition is the value of the tasks that coalition can perform: {a mathematical formula}v Γ (C)=u(T(C)).</a>
<a href="#4" id="4">Definition 13</a>
<a href="#5" id="5">Both TCSG and WTSG have special cases that are simple skill games.</a>
<a href="#6" id="6">These games require the number of completed tasks or the total weight of completed tasks to exceed a certain threshold value k for a coalition to win.</a>
